About True Religion Brand Jeans THE TRUE STORY: THE STITCH THAT STARTED IT ALL In 2002, True Religion emerged onto the Los Angeles denim scene by blowing up the construction of the classic five-pocket jean. Industry-standard sewing machines couldn't handle our designs, so we broke them apart and rebuilt them to produce our one-of-a-kind vision. With its five-needle thread at two-stitch-per-inch process, our Super T stitch was instantly recognized for style that was unlike any other denim brand in the world. True Religion's designs soon caught the attention of the world's most iconic style leaders, and demand for our denim grew rapidly. Everything from there on out was committed to be bigger, better, and bolder than the rest. As our stitching evolved, True Religion became synonymous with quality craftsmanship and bold style designed to stand out. Our specialty denim fits, washes & treatments, were all designed with amplified details to grab attention at every turn. Our iconic horseshoe was born from the silhouette of a Buddha's smile, and our hardware was inspired by the romance of denim's 140-year history. We have always been fashion forward, even from behind. Our styles inherit the swagger of their given name. The Joey. The Ricky. The Halle. However, it's the Fearless Style Leaders who rock True Religion with a Be So Bold attitude that ignite the world with bold statements of creative self-expression. We became famous because we were like no one before us, and what began with a stitch now leads to a future of innovative fashion designed by the fearless, for the fearless.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 9, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I dont know why there are complaints
reviews.reviewText: The quality of these jeans is excellent. The fit is superb. These are not selvedge. They can be washed. No dye ever came off on anything I ever sat on. No change ever came out of my pockets. And while I dont carry a knife like the other negative reviewer, what do you have in your pocket, a machete? I have 3.5 inch Kershaw that fits nicely. These are WELL MADE STYLISH jeans. IF you want jeans to do construction then buy the carharts like someone mentioned, and look like a construction worker.If you want a nice pair of jeans that you can wear out to dinner with a jacket or casually with a t shirt, look no further. True religion has styles from mild( im 52) to wild for my kids ( 19 and 16). Are they worth the dough over a pair of levis? You decide. I think so and I love my Levis too .

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 8, 2021
reviews.reviewText: I was bummed out I never buy clothes online but I figured I'll give it a try..I was so thrilled I ordered 30w 34 L the waist was perfect but the length was 28👀👀they looked like kids jeans...better luck next time I guess

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 6, 2021
reviews.reviewText: Was looking at Rock Reival (twice the price) but decided to try True Religion. I was so surprised. They fit perfectly and shipping was so fast. Gorgeous jeans and I saved so much money. Will definitely purchase more.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good quality and look
reviews.reviewText: The material is nice and doesn't feel or look cheap. The fit was as expected. This one is above your regular jeans and at the right price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 1, 2021
reviews.reviewText: The jeans were too big. I wished to purchase the correct size but the original price increased within a few days. Was there any way I could have made an exchange without paying the I crease?

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 25, 2020
reviews.reviewText: Gotta love these jeans. I get them a size up since I like my pants bagy but the sizes fit for me i love as well. The material and stitching are all wonderful on the pair I received and I especially liked that the pants are completely black to where you would realy have to be looking to see what jeans they are. The brand doesn't always need to be so flashy and I appreciate these more for being so.
